		<title>06THE USK CROSSING</title>
		<content>                                       
{ Usk}is an ancient{crossing point,}and
 some think a crossing at{Llanbadoc}was
 used untill the wooden bridge was     
 built, at the present site, in{1750.} 
                                       
   The{Romans}had a garrison here which
 protected the river crossinge and the 
 town has grown around it, mainly on   
 the east side.                        
                                       
 The stone bridge with five arches was 
 recently improved so that the water   
 flows through more easily, as part of 
 the{flood prevention scheme.          
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
